OL,5,G0600 James Martin's French Adventure
OL,6,     FThe chef arrives in the riverside
OL,7,     Ftown of L'Isle-sur-la-Sorgue in
OL,8,     Fsouth-eastern France, where his
OL,9,     Fculinary hero Keith Floyd once
OL,10,     Fowned a restaurant. Buying produce
OL,11,     Ffrom its floating market, and a
OL,12,     FFloyd-style hat, James sets up his
OL,13,     Fmobile kitchen on a bridge
OL,14,     Foverlooking the river, and cooks
OL,15,     Fpeaches pain perdu in the
OL,16,     Fsunshine. Heading back in the
OL,17,     Fdirection of the town, James
OL,18,     Fsamples some truffle-laden dishes
OL,19,     Fat renowned restaurant La
OL,20,     FBeaugraviere
